---
title: Figure 3.8 — Séquence — Caution, exécution, preuves et validation
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Prestataire
    actor Client
    participant FE as Angular
    participant API as Django REST
    participant ESC as EscrowService
    participant MM as MetaMask
    participant SC as EscrowContract
    participant WS as WebSocket<br/>Channels

    Prestataire->>FE: Postule à la mission
    FE->>API: POST /api/missions/{id}/apply/
    API-->>FE: Candidature pending

    Client->>FE: Accepte la candidature
    FE->>API: POST /api/missions/{id}/accept_application/
    API-->>FE: status=accepted, deposit_deadline=+4h

    Prestataire->>FE: Dépose caution (solde FCFA)
    FE->>API: POST /api/missions/{id}/pay_deposit/
    API->>ESC: lock_provider_deposit()
    API-->>FE: deposit_paid=true

    opt Ancrage caution on-chain
        FE->>MM: acceptMission(missionContractId)
        MM->>SC: Transaction
        FE->>API: POST .../record-provider-deposit/
    end

    Prestataire->>FE: Démarrer la mission
    FE->>API: POST /api/missions/{id}/start/
    API-->>FE: status=in_progress

    loop Suivi GPS
        Prestataire->>WS: Position GPS
        WS-->>Client: Mise à jour temps réel
    end

    Prestataire->>FE: Upload photos + Finaliser
    FE->>API: POST /api/missions/{id}/submit_proof/
    API-->>FE: status=submitted

    opt Ancrage preuve on-chain
        FE->>MM: submitProof(missionId, proofHash)
        FE->>API: POST .../record-proof/
    end

    Client->>FE: Valide la mission
    FE->>API: POST /api/missions/{id}/validate/
    API->>ESC: release_payment_to_provider()
    API-->>FE: status=completed, 95% libérés
